LC,

I understand where you are coming from in respect in speaking their 
opinion, however if i had to read yet another post of how great 
someone is when nobody is great in this i was going to be sick.  
Arrogance and ego is very bad and that kind of mentality is Cancer to 
this research, i can share my opinion with the group but never tell 
anybody what to do.  I sit idly by and watch 200+ people get bad 
information on a daily basis, which hurts any good research.  The 
best way to go about what we are doing is to come up with our own 
theories and post them as examples for others to read.  We shouldn&#39;t 
have anybody dictate every aspect of this as fact.  If anybody can 
give information on box use it would be Frank, who nobody who owns 
boxes has listened to...myself included.  He knows how they work and 
offers a great amount of knowledge to this subject or else none of us 
would even be here.  This board has started to be a dictatorship of 
one persons opinion and if nobody listened...they were wrong.  And to 
me, that&#39;s wrong.  I started out with Joe&#39;s box and moved forward and 
nobody helped me in my path.  I since aquired other boxes and taught 
myself them as well, which means it can be done.  People...do your 
own thing and get results the best way you can and learn from your 
mistakes, that&#39;s what i did.  And getting Bruce his first Joe&#39;s box 
and Frank&#39;s box and getting him started in box research, i somewhat 
feel responsible for what transpired on this board and i apologize to 
those involved.  Frank, i&#39;m sorry that another person has taken your 
box and claimed to know all and not listening to what you adhere we 
do.

Nuff Said,
-Steve H.


